      "content": "But isn't saying we should \"pair\" social programs with \"robust, punitive measures\" just a way of saying that we shouldn't move away from the punitive model? It feels like you're framing the punitive approach as the essential foundation and everything else as just a secondary supplement. Can't you just admit that the \"tough on crime\" ideology is inherently flawed because it prioritizes punishment over the actual root causes of crime?",
